As an additional preliminary step, we have tested our code against exact analytical results valid for small $N=4$ (tetramers) and $N=5$ (pentamers) \cite{Taylor95,Taylor03,Magee08} at different vaues of the interaction range $\lambda$, finding again perfect agreement.

Further support stems from a comparison with the Molecular Dynamics (MD) and canonical MonteCarlo (MC) results by Zhou and Karplus \cite{Zhou97}, as seen in  Fig.~\ref{fig:fig4} (top) for $8\le N \le 64$, and can be contrasted against Figure 3 of Ref.~ \cite{Zhou97}, again with extremely good agreement.

